text: Replaced 3 MOVs in stack. Replaced all snubber caps with 5KV caps. Installed right side gate drive boards.

title: All three BTS ACMs showed trigger rate of 11.11 Hz - reset OK
All three BTS ACMs showed trigger rate of 11.11 Hz; reset all OK
text: The 10Hz extraction trigger for BTS ACMs comes from SRS BTS-DG2. Since all three ACMs tripped with exactly the same value, all three get the trigger in parallel, and that SRS has already been swapped out, it seems likely that the glitch originates with the 10Hz pulse feeding the SRS.

title: Shift summary: Saturday swing
text: SUMMARY: User beam for all of this 12-hour shift. Average fill rate was around 43mA/minute, average calculated efficiency was around 93%. There was one missed fill due to a BTS ACM trip (all three ACMs) when there was no beam. INJECTOR: 300mV Q, no tuning needed. All three BTS ACMs tripped shortly before the 11:10pm fill, when there was no beam through the chopper. All of them displayed a trigger fault (11.11Hz). SPEAR: 500mA autofill topoffs every 5 minutes, as scheduled. There was one missed fill due to the BTS ACM trip.

text: Dave asked to calibrate klystron heater for this station. Connected pulse and triax HV cables. Removed all the ground hooks inside the modulator. Removed the blue lock for CB7, but I couldn't remove the 120Vac because I have no key for this blue lock? Therefore, I stopped work, installed ground hooks back and blue lock for CB7. Also there was no VVS.

title: Linac West Interlock Checks Update:
text: We got through most of the interlock checks that were not checked Thursday 11/13. What is left to initially check as of 11/14: PPS Warning System Statuses: All Search resets, zone clear statuses, housing lights flashing and audible warning alarms - Presets: PR-7E, PR-5H, PR-3H - Sector 6 , yellow light, Manway Door and Hatch Statuses (the search key from sector 4 was unable to be turned in the keypod, could have done this in permitted but I forgot that this was possible) - Sectors 5-1 yellow light - Sector 4 yellow light and annunciator status - Sector 0: Manway Checks, Keybank checks Left to recheck with new procedural edits: - 0/1 boundary gate door checks + SAT Level Checks - Any fixes that were implemented from 11/13 CATERs that would require re-checking interlocks in the field New CATERS as of 11/14: 154603 - Sector 10A key-banks have keys that will not release 154604 - Sector 6 manway does not allow the sector 4 search key to turn in its key-pod. 154605 - The sector 4 right key-bank only allows personnel keys to be released when the search key is in. Procedural Edits: I have put comments and made slight changes to the interlock checklist via sharepoint Those included changing the language for the emergency entry/exit paddles to pull, instead of push and hold, as well as formatting comments: The AOR Interlock check tables have strange formatting that is only viewable in print preview that changes the structure of the document when printed.
